  "prompt": "What is the best time of day to drink a single coffee to keep you going for the longest duration?",
  "response": "According to scientific research, the optimal time to drink coffee for sustained alertness is typically between 9:30-11:30 AM. Here's why:\n\n1. Cortisol levels: Most people's natural cortisol levels (a hormone that makes you feel alert) peak between 8-9 AM. Drinking coffee during peak cortisol can reduce caffeine's effectiveness.\n\n2. Mid-morning timing: Around 9:30-11:30 AM, cortisol levels start to dip, making caffeine most effective at boosting energy and alertness.\n\n3. Sustained effect: Caffeine takes about 15-45 minutes to enter your bloodstream and typically remains effective for 3-5 hours.\n\n4. Afternoon crash prevention: By consuming coffee mid-morning, you can help prevent the typical afternoon energy slump.\n\nAdditional tips:\n- Avoid drinking coffee immediately after waking up\n- Don't consume caffeine late in the day (after 2 PM) as it can disrupt sleep\n- Individual variations exist, so adjust based on your personal physiology and schedule\n\nRemember, everyone's body responds differently to caffeine, so you might need to experiment to find your ideal timing.",
